 <item> <title>Ohio to Receive More Than $132 Million to Turn Around Its Persistently Lowest Achieving Schools</title>
 <link>https://www.ed.gov/news/press-releases/ohio-receive-more-132-million-turn-around-its-persistently-lowest-achieving-schools</link>
 <description>U.S. Secretary of Education Arne Duncan today announced that Ohio will receive more than $132 million to turn around its persistently lowest achieving schools through the School Improvement Grants (SIG) program. These funds are part of the $3.5 billion that will be made available to states this spring from money set aside in the 2009 budget and the American Recovery and Reinvestment Act.</description>
 <guid isPermaLink="false">https://www.ed.gov/news/press-releases/ohio-receive-more-132-million-turn-around-its-persistently-lowest-achieving-schools</guid>
