 <item> <title>Ohio to Receive More Than $483 Million in Additional Recovery Funds</title>
 <link>https://www.ed.gov/news/press-releases/ohio-receive-more-483-million-additional-recovery-funds</link>
 <description>U. S. Secretary of Education Arne Duncan today announced that an additional $483,024,288 is now available for Ohio under the American Recovery and Reinvestment Act (ARRA) of 2009.  To date, Ohio has received $2,986,873,388 through the Recovery Act. The state recently reported that recovery dollars have been used to provide funding for more than 11,800 education jobs from Oct. 1 to Dec.</description>
